    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's the complete implementation plan for the `rename` feature across all 4 files:\n\n### What I found in the codebase\n\n- **`api/types.go:761–765`** — `CopyRequest` is the exact pattern to mirror for `RenameRequest`\n- **`api/client.go:382–387`** — `Client.Copy()` is the exact template for `Client.Rename()`\n- **`server/routes.go:1446–1483`** — `CopyHandler` provides name parsing/validation pattern (uses `model.ParseName` → `getExistingName` → `CopyModel`)\n- **`server/routes.go:1055–1104`** — `DeleteHandler` provides the manifest remove pattern (`manifest.ParseNamedManifest` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()`)\n- **`server/routes.go:1698`** — `/api/copy` route is where `/api/rename` should be inserted\n- **`cmd/cmd.go:1338–1350`** — `CopyHandler` / `copyCmd` are the exact templates for the CLI additions\n- **No new imports needed** anywhere — all packages already exist in each file\n\n### 7-step implementation\n1. **`api/types.go`** — Add `RenameRequest{Source, Destination string}` after `CopyRequest` (line 765)\n2. **`api/client.go`** — Add `Client.Rename()` calling `c.do(POST, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)` after `Client.Copy()` (line 387)\n3. **`server/routes.go`** — Add `Server.RenameHandler()`: validates empty fields (400), validates names via `model.ParseName`/`.IsValid()` with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg` (400), checks destination already exists via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest` (409), calls `CopyModel` (404/500 on error), calls `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` (500 on error), returns 200 `{\"status\":\"success\"}`\n4. **`server/routes.go`** — Add `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after the `/api/copy` line in `GenerateRoutes()`\n5. **`cmd/cmd.go`** — Add `RenameHandler` function after `CopyHandler` (line 1350), printing `Renamed \"SOURCE\" to \"DESTINATION\"`\n6. **`cmd/cmd.go`** — Add `renameCmd` cobra.Command after `copyCmd` (line 2263), with `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n7. **`cmd/cmd.go`** — Register `renameCmd` in both the env-docs loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand()`, placed after `copyCmd` in each",
